Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Hamilton Sinkler designs and manufactures architectural hardware for the luxury consumer. They produce striking, innovative designs in collaboration with artists willing to interpret their visions in door and cabinet hardware. Founded in New York City in 2001, Hamilton Sinkler has established itself as a forward-thinking boutique firm with excellent service, technical expertise, unique design vision, and state of the art manufacturing capabilities. Their elegant hardware adorns New York high rises, luxury town and country homes, boutique hotels, corporate headquarters, department stores, and more throughout North America. Its founders, twin brothers Rob and Ash Suri, emigrated to New York from London, England after receiving their educations in building studies and civil engineering. From their family roots in India they draw on the country’s rich history of artisanship and expert metalwork techniques to create exquisite decorative hardware with architectural chops. In 2007, creative entrepreneur Chris Burch joined as a business partner, and The Hamilton Decorative Collection became Hamilton Sinkler in honor of Burch’s late mother. Today, Rob Suri serves as the chief operating officer while Ash leads a prestigious New York luxury home building and renovating company, Autun Contractors.  Located steps from New York City’s Design Center, the Hamilton Sinkler team strives to provide excellent service and technical expertise. From hardware scheduling services to 3-D modelling, they offer an unparalleled experience while shepherding the client through each step of the design and purchasing process. Hamilton Sinkler products are available at hand-picked decorative showrooms throughout the United States, Canada, Mexico and select countries worldwide.

Description: Saint Clair Group is a construction management firm.
Full Description: Saint Clair Group is a full-service construction management firm that guides clients through every step of their project -- from concept to completion. Thanks to our flexibility and client-forward mindset, our clients can be as involved or hands-off as they prefer. We provide top-tier services in specialties, including but not limited to owner’s representation, end-to-end design-build contracts, and cannabis consulting.  At Saint Clair Group, you supply the idea and set your budget, and we take care of the rest -- no matter how unusual your proposal might be. Our team isn’t afraid of taking on complex construction management projects and frequently oversees projects with heavy mechanical, electrical, and plumbing requirements. We have a wealth of experience working in Commercial, Residential, and Historical Construction and can readily address complex assignments relating to Design-Build Services, Federal Contracts, Site and Building Assessments, and Zoning Review and Compliance. Saint Clair Group has also developed a distinguished reputation for its expertise in cannabis consulting. Our team has been at the forefront of the cannabis construction industry since it first took root in the mid-2000s. We know how to build top-of-the-line grow-processing facilities and dispensaries from the ground up -- and, just as critically, we know how to do so while keeping cost and expediency in mind. Our cannabis-specific experience spans the gamut from application writing and review to cannabis facilities construction and management, dispensary design and construction, site and building compliance review, cannabis MEP design and installation, and facility security and GMP compliance.  In the cannabis specialty and beyond, we can relieve our clients of their project management burdens and ensure that they have the best possible team for the job. Saint Clair Group’s extensive connections with local architects, general contractors, engineers, and other specialists allow us to make decisions based solely on our client’s best interests.  Saint Clair Group is based in Lancaster, PA.
